dc_description_s: This point shapefile was created by mapping just the "center" coordinates listed for artificial reefs as noted in the California Department Fish and Wildlife Guide to Artificial Reefs of Southern California. This coverage identifies centroid locations of artificial reefs along the California coast and primarily in Southern California. California. Department of Fish and Game. Marine Resources Region. (2007). California Coastal Artificial Reefs, 2007. California. Department of Fish and Game. Marine Resources Region. Attributes updated 10/03/2012 This layer is presented in the WGS84 coordinate system for web display purposes. Downloadable data are provided in native coordinate system or projection.
